Very creative and clearly professionally executed. The two characters that wander through the book (but are not specifically mentioned in the text) always say the letter name and each one has a different voice. The single-tap words and pictures are clearly distinct recordings, versus being spliced from the reading. Fun sound effects. Vera's Violin sound warrants (and demonstrates) Suess' "very very very awful." Only suggestion is a method of going directly to a specific letter versus paging through.
